When I join a Freenode channel via the webchat.freenode.net, I see the following message displayed across the top:<p>&quot;&quot;&quot;
Welcome to the freenode autonomous zone, the home of freedom. | Speak English | For help, #help | BBS, #freenode-bbs | Jobs, #freenode-jobs | IRC.com, #irc | BNC, #freenode-bnc | Remotes, #remotes | Freedom means a lot including the freedom for ops to kick&#x2F;ban whoever the f** they want. Act sensibly or get f**ed.
&quot;&quot;&quot;<p>That kind of tone towards people is, frankly, offensive.<p>Is this message displaying on all IRC clients that connect to Freenode, or just the webchat.freenode.net?
